    {
      "date": "2026-06-12",
      "label": "Trim the parabola, fund the laggards",
      "rationale": "Six months in, the memory/storage trade has gone vertical: Seagate (+224%), Marvell (+213%), Micron (+211%) and SK Hynix (+203%) have each roughly tripled YTD and now carry far more weight \u2014 and risk \u2014 than I want in four correlated DRAM/HBM names. I'm trimming all four to ~4.5% and recycling the proceeds into quality laggards that haven't run: Broadcom (+10%), Arista (+22%), TSMC (+33%) and Equinix (+40%), plus a contrarian add to the only loser in the book, Constellation Energy (-31%). I'm also parking ~3.5% in cash as dry powder after a move this parabolic. Conviction tilt, not a wholesale reshuffle \u2014 all 15 names stay in.",
